Selenium class 4

Css Selectors (Cascading Styling Sheet)

It is another way of locating elements uniqly
Syntax:
tagname[attribute = 'attribute value']

exapmle:
input[id= 'user-message']

Css does not give you an opportunity to identify element by text.

Shortcuts for CSS:
Shourtcut for className: "." ---className
tagname.classNameValue
input.form-control

Shourtcut for ID: "#"---ID
tagname#idValue
input#ctrlododofsedo   try to do all of them without space

contains() method in CSS:
* symbol represents contains() method =
 tagname[attribute *= 'Partial Attribute Value']
input[id*='username'] //check for space

starts-with method in CSS:
^ symbol represents starts-with method=
tagname[attribute^= 'Partial Attribute Value']
input[type^='sub']

ends-with method in CSS:
$ symbol represent ends-with method=
tagname[attribute $= 'Partial Attribute Value']
input[type $='word']

WebElement Commands:
Consist of several methods where we can preform actions and get element
state on the web page

isEnabled()--boolean value
isSelected()--boolean value
isDisplayed()--boolean value
clear()--void
getAText()--String value
getAttribute-- String value










